{
    "id": 1020098,
    "name": "Avoid creating cookie with overly broad path (Javascript)",
    "href": "AIP/quality-rules/1020098",
    "critical": true,
    "severity": 20,
    "maxWeight": 7,
    "extension": {
        "name": "com.castsoftware.html5",
        "href": "AIP/extensions/com.castsoftware.html5"
    },
    "associatedValueName": "Number of violation occurrences",
    "description": "This rule checks that the cookies do not have an overly broad path, such as the root context path (\"/\").",
    "output": "Associated to each violation, the following information is provided:\n- The number of violation occurrences\n- Bookmarks for violation occurrences found in the source code",
    "rationale": "If read access is not properly restricted, then attackers can steal sensitive information. If write access is not properly restricted, then attackers can modify and possibly delete the data, causing incorrect results and possibly a denial of service.\n\nCookies with an overly broad path, such as the root context path (\"/\"), can be accessed by all web applications on the same domain name. A cookie with sensitive data, but with too broad a path, could hence be read and tampered by a less secure and untrusted application.",
    "reference": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/287.html \nhttps://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10_2013-A6-Sensitive_Data_Exposure \nhttps://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10-2017_A3-Sensitive_Data_Exposure",
    "remediation": "Do not provide a root path",
    "remediationSample": "// specifc path is recommended \ndocument.cookie = \"name=test; path=/admin\";",
    "sample": "// root path is not recommended \ndocument.cookie = \"name=test; path=/\";",
    "total": "Number of JavaScript Functions assigning document.cookie",
    "alternativeName": "Ensure you do not allow access to all domain when defining cookie path",
